From 9368c76a383d3a9d9a1de27bf364587755dc38db Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shayne Chen <shayne.chen@mediatek.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2026 17:48:26 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 72/89] mtk: mt76: mt7996: support MLO reconfig

Add MLO R1 reconfiguration support.
R2 is not yet implemented.


mtk: mt76: mt7996: set mlink->wcid to NULL after link removed

This fixes scan after station disconnection.

Signed-off-by: Shayne Chen <shayne.chen@mediatek.com>

mtk: mt7996: always use an empty link_id for allocating scanning mlink

This fixes the following potential crash:
- AP: 2g non-MLD AP
- STA: configured as two-link 2+5g MLD STA

Steps:
- Establish connection
- Although STA is configured as MLD, it'll be non-MLD 2g after connection
- Trigger scan on STA 5g band
- Crash happens since 5g band scanning tries to use occupied link_id 0 and
  directly return from mt7996_vif_link_add()

Signed-off-by: Shayne Chen <shayne.chen@mediatek.com>
